    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks for your reply! Apologize if I seems silly, but could you be more specific? I guess your idea is to prove <code>normalClosure F K₁interK₂ K ≤ normalClosure F K₁ K = K₁</code> and <code>normalClosure F K₁interK₂ K ≤ normalClosure F K₂ K = K₂</code> using <code> IntermediateField.normalClosure_mono</code>. But  </p>\n<p><code>IntermediateField.normalClosure_mono.{u_3, u_1} {F : Type u_1} {L : Type u_3} [Field F] [Field L] [Algebra F L] (K K' : IntermediateField F L) [Normal F L] (h : K ≤ K') : normalClosure F (↥K) L ≤ normalClosure F (↥K') L</code></p>\n<p>where <code>(F := F) (K := K₁interK₂) (K' := K₁) (L := K)</code> in this case requires instance <code>[Normal F L]</code>(in this case <code>[Normal F K]</code>). How to reach that?</p>",
        "id": 455000996,
