    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, sorry, this was more thorny than I expected. I ended up proving it directly (similar to your approach) so that the result can go into <code>Normal.lean</code> rather than <code>NormalClosure.lean</code>. Here's the PR: <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/15290\">#15290</a>. I found it helpful to prove the converse direction of <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=IntermediateField.splits_of_splits#doc\">docs#IntermediateField.splits_of_splits</a>, so that it can be applied to the hypotheses and the conclusion. For algebraicity, I used <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Algebra.IsAlgebraic.of_injective#doc\">docs#Algebra.IsAlgebraic.of_injective</a>.</p>",
